  "A disease affects 1% of a population. A test is 99% accurate (true positive and true negative). If a person tests positive, the probability they actually have the disease is approximately:": "",
  "About 50%": "",
  "1%": "",
  "99%": "",
  "About 90%": "",
  "By Bayes' Theorem: P(disease|+) = (0.99×0.01)/((0.99×0.01)+(0.01×0.99)) = 0.0099/(0.0099+0.0099) = 0.50. When the disease is rare, even accurate tests produce many false positives.": "",
